name: src/main.js

types: {"backend": string, "flavor": string, "suffixGroup": string, "suffixFn": function, "minSuffix": number, "minSuffixSigfigs": *, "maxSmall": *, "sigfigs": number, "format": string}

params.name: opts.flavor
params.description: 'full' or 'short'. Flavors can modify any number of other options here. Full is the default; short has fewer sigfigs and shorter standard-suffixes.

params.name: opts.maxSmall
params.description: Special formatting for numbers with a decimal point

return.description: which suffix to use for this number in a list of suffixes. You can also think of this as "how many commas are in the number?"
The suffix that this number would use, with no number shown.

params.name: opts
params.description: Override the options provided to the Formatter constructor.

name: formatFlavor
description:
Format a number with a specified flavor. It's very common to call the formatter with different flavors, so it has its own shortcut.

`Formatter.formatFull()` and `Formatter.formatShort()` are also available.

return.description: The complete list of formats available. Use this to build an options UI to allow your players to choose their favorite format.

name: format
description: Format a number using the default options.

name: formatFull
description: Format a full-flavor number using the default options. Identical to `format()`

name: formatShort
description: Format a short-flavor number using the default options.
